coverage-data-packet-rssi-threshold.description: Configure Received Signal Strength Indicator(RSSI) threshold value for data packets in dBm.

coverage-voice-packet-rssi-threshold.description: Configure Received Signal Strength Indicator(RSSI) threshold value for voice packets in dBm.

exception-level.description: Configure the coverage exception level in percentage of total clients to actual failed clients.

band-select-client-rssi.description:
Configure minimum mobile station Received Signal Strength Indicator(RSSI) threshold in dBm.
         Mobile stations having RSSI below this value will not be recorded in the suppressed table.
         This configuration filters out far away mobile stations with weaker signal strength. This will limit the number of mobile stations on the table to a reasonable amount.

band-select-client-mid-rssi.description: Configure medium mobile station Received Signal Strength Indicator(RSSI) threshold in dBm. Mobile station between this value and cldband_select_client_rssi will be recorded in suppressed table but will not be denied. The mobile station having RSSI stronger this value will be recorded and denied.

band-select-cycle-count.description: Configure maximum number of cycles not responding.

band-select-cycle-threshold.description: Configure cycle threshold for band select in milliseconds.

band-select-age-out-dual-band.description: Configure expire of dual band in secs.

band-select-age-out-suppression.description: Configure expire of suppression in secs.

band-select-probe-response.description:
Configure Access-Point(AP)'s probe response with clients to verify whether client can associate on both 2.4 GHz and 5 Ghz spectrum.
         When set to true, AP suppresses probe response to new clients for all Service Set Identifier(SSID)'s that are not being Band Select disabled.

dca-contribution-interference.description: Configure Dynamic Channel Assignment (DCA) for Radio-Frequency(RF)-Profiles.

rf-dca-chan-width.description:
Specify the system Dynamic Channel Assignment (DCA) channel width selection for the Radio-Frequency(RF)-Profile
         Possible values:
         rf-dca-chan-width-20-mhz  =  Channel width will be set to 20 Mhz
         rf-dca-chan-width-40-mhz  =  Channel width will be set to 40 Mhz
         rf-dca-chan-width-80-mhz  =  Channel width will be set to 80 Mhz
         rf-dca-chan-width-best    =  Best channel width will be selected by Dynamic Channel Assignment (DCA) algorithm
         rf-dca-chan-width-160-mhz =  Channel width will be set to 160 Mhz

load-balancing-window.description: Configure number of clients associated between Access-Point(AP)'s.

load-balancing-denial-count.description: Configure number of clients denial with respect to Access-Point(AP).

trap-threshold-clients.description:
Configure threshold number of clients per Access-Point(AP) radio to trigger a trap.
         The trap ciscoLwappApClientThresholdNotify will be triggered once the count of clients on the AP radio reaches this limit.
         A value of zero indicates that the trap is disabled.

trap-threshold-interference.description: Configure interference threshold in (%) traps are generated when interference exceeds this value .

trap-threshold-noise.description: Configure threshold number of noise threshold between -127 and 0 dBm.

trap-threshold-utilization.description: Configure threshold of bandwidth (%) being utilized by an access-point. Traps are sent when this value is exceeded

max-radio-clients.description: Configure maximum number of radio clients per Access-Point(AP) in high density environment.

multicast-data-rate.description: Configure minimum data rate at which multicast clients can associate to Access-Point(AP). A value 0 indicates that AP will automatically adjust data rates.

rx-sen-sop-threshold.description: Configure the Receiver Start of Packet(RX-SOP) sensitivity threshold

rx-sen-sop-custom.description: Rx SOP custom values configured between -85 dBm (default) and -60 dBm. This configured value takes effect only when rx sop threshold is set to custom

client-network-preference.description:
Configure the client network preference. Possible values are:
         1. connectivity - Radio-Resource-Management(RRM) Algorithm has a preference on connectivity of the clients.
         2. throughput   - Radio-Resource-Management(RRM) Algorithm has a preference on high throughput of the clients.
         3. default      - Radio-Resource-Management(RRM) Algorithm has no preference on the clients.

hsr-mode.description: Configure High-speed roam(HSR) mode for Radio-Frequency(RF) profile.

hsr-neighbor-timeout.description: Configure timeout interval of neighbors that will be configured for Radio-Frequency(RF) profile. Neighbor timeout factor will be five times the neighbor interval

opt-roam-rssi-treshold.description: Configure the minimum Received Signal Strength Indicator(RSSI) threshold for optimized roaming to occur. Possible values are in the range -127 dbm to 0 dbm

opt-roam-rssi-check-enable.description: Indicates if Received Signal Strength Indicator(RSSI) threshold is enabled before optimized roaming is enabled

atf-oper-mode.description:
Configure air time fairness operating mode.
         Possible values:
         apf-atf-mode-disable = Disable the Air Time Fairness.
         apf-atf-mode-ssid    = Configure airtime-fairness in enforce-policy mode.
         apf-atf-mode-monitor = Monitor Mode represented by cLApDot11IfType of ATF supported APs joined in the controller

atf-optimization.description:
Configure air time fairness Optimization Policy represented by cLApDot11IfType of ATF supported APs.
         Possible values:
         apf-atf-stealing-policy-disable = Disable airtime-fairness optimization
         apf-atf-stealing-policy-enable  = Enable airtime-fairness optimization

bridge-client-access.description: Airtime Allocation Mode under Radio-Frequency(rf)-profile. Value = True, indicates Airtime Allocation feature is enabled and Value = False, indicates Airtime Allocation feature is disabled.

client-aware-fra.description: Client aware FRA allows the Dual band to operate on 5 Ghz or monitor mode depending on the load on the dedicated 5 Ghz radio

client-select-threshold.description: Client aware FRA utilization threshold value for moving Dual band radio from monitor mode to to Client Serving

client-reset-threshold.description: Client aware FRA utilization threshold value for moving Dual band radio from Client Serving mode to Monitor mode

he-non-srg-obss-pd-max.description: Non-SRG OBSS PD maximum threshold in dBm

ndp-mode.description:
Neighbor discovery protocol operating mode  configuration.
         Possible values are:
         auto        - AP does neighbor discovery either on serving channel or
                       off channel based on its NDP capability
         off-channel - AP does neighbor discovery on off channel

psc-bias.description: Enable or disable preferred scanning channel bias for 6 GHz DCA

he-srg-obss-pd-enable.description: Enable/Disable 802.11ax SRG OBSS PD spatial reuse

he-srg-obss-pd-min.description: SRG OBSS PD minimum threshold in dBm

he-srg-obss-pd-max.description: SRG OBSS PD maximum threshold in dBm

guard-interval-ext.description: Set guard interval for rf profile

client-reset-thresh-6ghz.description: Client aware FRA utilization threshold value for moving dual band radio from 6GHz to 5GHz

client-count-reset-6ghz.description: Client aware FRA client count value for moving dual band radio from 6GHz to 5GHz

channel-width-min.description: Minimum Channel Width Allowed for Dynamic Bandwidth Selection. Possible values are 20,40,80 and Maximum allowed

channel-width-max.description: Maximum Channel Width Allowed for Dynamic Bandwidth Selection. Possible values are 20,40,80 and Maximum allowed

std-pwr-mode-allowed.description: Allow AP to operate in 6GHz standard power mode

fra-action.description: FRA action for dual band radio

ampdu-window-size.description: Window size for aggregate MAC protocol data unit

management-retries.description: Radio parameters for management frame retries

aggregate-retries.description: Radio parameters for aggregate frame retries

non-aggregate-retries.description: Radio parameters for non-aggregate frame retries

unii3-lp-channels.description: Enable/Disable UNII-3 low power channels for 5 GHz band
